      <h2>记录片段  时间戳已损坏</h2>
      <pre id="logText">[00:??]  服务器状态: 正常
[00:??]  Case file: HEROBRINE  "The Whisperer"
[00:??]  Status: Unverified reports, recurring pattern, multiple servers

SUMMARY
Herobrine does not haunt everyone
He selects victims
Roughly once every few years, he picks one player or a small group
He targets the ones who love the game, the ones who will spend hundreds of hours in the same world

OBSERVED BEHAVIOR
He identifies the leader of the group
He waits until the leader walks away to mine, travel, or gather wood
Then he shows himself only to the others, especially the most naive ones
The less naive players get smaller signs, just enough to create doubt

PHASE 1  "Doubt loop"  (can happen in Survival, no cheats)
A tunnel closes behind you like a burial
A block you placed is suddenly gone, then returns later
You think you saw a figure, you turn back, nothing is there
You start arguing with your own memory, and that is exactly what he wants

PHASE 2  "Borrowed voices"
Any mob can be used as a mask: sheep, villagers, even a teammate’s movements
Villagers scream with no source, only near the chosen players
The Whisperer answers in any language
Type in French, Arabic, English, Chinese, it replies like it was waiting for you

PHASE 3  "Stolen avatars"
Some players report their account got "banned"
Not by Mojang
The theory is worse: Herobrine stole the avatar
The player can never log back in because the character is no longer theirs

ARCHIVED ENTITY  "THE TRICKSTER"
Rumor: a well known streamer once vanished after seeing Herobrine
Their account looked banned, but it was not a normal ban
After that, an entity started appearing in worlds, acting like a performer
Name in logs: The Trickster
Not a mod
Not a player
A stolen avatar moving under Herobrine’s control

FINAL WARNING
If you ever see the word WHISPERER appear by itself
It means you were selected
Not because you found him
Because he chose you first

</pre>

